---
import MinimalLayout from "@/layouts/MinimalLayout.astro";
---

<MinimalLayout title="Abdulla Al Bassam" active="about">
  <section class="about">
    <p>
      I'm Abdulla Al Bassam, a final-year Cybersecurity and Networking student at
      <a href="https://www.northumbria.ac.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Northumbria University</a>,
      Newcastle, on track for a First Class Honours degree. I'm a recipient of
      the Saudi government's <em>Emdad</em> Scholarship.
    </p>

    <p>
      My final-year project sits at the intersection of machine learning and
      cybersecurity: an adversarially robust spam detection system using a
      fine-tuned <strong>DistilBERT</strong> transformer deployed inside a
      secure mail server pipeline, evaluating how intelligent systems can be
      hardened against manipulation.
    </p>

    <p>
      Across my degree I've worked hands-on in penetration testing, defensive
      security, enterprise networking, digital forensics, and secure software
      architecture — vulnerability assessments with Nmap and Burp Suite,
      defensive controls with iptables and Snort, multi-site WANs with MPLS VPN
      and IPsec in GNS3, forensic investigations with Autopsy and Volatility 3,
      and a secure REST API built from scratch. Outside of university I sharpen
      offensive skills through CTF challenges on <strong>TryHackMe</strong> and
      <strong>Hack The Box</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
      On the side, I founded <strong>Sweaty</strong>, a social platform for
      gamers that I designed and developed end-to-end with React Native —
      reviews, ratings, curated lists, a real-time social feed, AI-powered
      recommendations, and game-library importing. The app is currently in
      pilot testing before public release.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm a member of the <strong>Claude Builder Club</strong> at Northumbria,
      where I work on agentic AI development and automation projects, and I
      hold certifications from Anthropic and Google in AI prototyping and
      agentic development. Whether it's security, software, or AI, I'm drawn
      to building things that work, breaking things that don't, and
      understanding the theory behind both.
    </p>

    <h2 class="block-heading">Education</h2>
    <ul class="entries">
      <li>
        <div class="entry-row">
          <div>
            <strong>BSc (Hons) Networks &amp; Cyber Security</strong>
            <span class="muted"> · Northumbria University</span>
          </div>
          <span class="meta">2023 — 2026</span>
        </div>
        <p class="muted small">Predicted: First Class Honours.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="entry-row">
          <div>
            <strong>Foundation Year — Economics &amp; Mathematics</strong>
            <span class="muted"> · King's College London</span>
          </div>
          <span class="meta">2022 — 2023</span>
        </div>
        <p class="muted small">Grade: 2:1.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="entry-row">
          <div>
            <strong>American Diploma with Honours</strong>
            <span class="muted"> · Modern Knowledge Schools, Bahrain</span>
          </div>
          <span class="meta">2008 — 2022</span>
        </div>
        <p class="muted small">98% Overall GPA.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="block-heading">Currently</h2>
    <ul class="bullets">
      <li>Finishing my dissertation on adversarially robust spam detection.</li>
      <li>Pilot-testing <strong>Sweaty</strong> ahead of its public release.</li>
      <li>Working through the <strong>eJPT</strong>, with <strong>OSCP</strong> on the longer-term roadmap.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</MinimalLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .about strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about em {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .block-heading {
    font-family: "Space Grotesk", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--cloudy-deep);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .entries {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .entries > li {
    padding: 0.7rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .entries > li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .entry-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .entry-row strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .meta {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", "SF Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--cloudy-deep);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .muted {
    color: var(--cloudy-deep);
  }

  .small {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin: 0.3rem 0 0;
  }

  .bullets {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
  }

  .bullets li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
